choices.text: a personal and religious matter, voice the "Pro"-force of the issue over the "anti" male perspective. The majority of German men you observe assume and assert themselves as uninvolved bystanders, both personally and intellectually opposed to abortion. There is no public outlet whereby rebuttals to their 'Pro-life' justifications are enacted. During my physical self-defense lessons from a female Molotov thrown, I considered next to taking my aggressor to the ground. It was easy to quickly acknowledge it was a crazy idea; the dude was no walk in the park. For one, he was furious about this transgression I had apparently initiated to his body. For another, there's literally zero likelihood he was as out of shape as I was. I probably hadn't worked out for a solid three months with some random cardio here and there, stacked up in humiliating belches when I accidentally sparked my inhaler to gain down to the pharmacy and work my way out of embarrassment. Meanwhile, this guy was within shouting distance of competing at Mr. Universe. I was about to claim the seat of Mr. Liberto, a seat I considered myself fairly well-insulated already: a college graduate with a mere 1.5 degrees – instead of Augie's plethora of thirty – with a girlfriend for over a year in which I only felt shame about a statistic every month behind my woman during her time of the month. The prospect of engaging had me laughing because of how improbable the situation was
